## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This FSD specifies the functional behavior of the Kotlin Graph Engine module. It defines use cases, business rules, data specifications, API contracts, and integration requirements for building and querying call graphs and dependency graphs on JVM.

### 1.2 Scope

* Call graph construction from AST/symbol data
* Dependency graph construction from import statements
* Graph traversal algorithms (BFS, DFS, shortest path)
* Impact analysis (change propagation)
* Cycle detection (circular dependencies, recursive calls)
* Hot path identification (centrality metrics)
* Incremental graph updates
* MCP tool interface for graph queries

