## 3. Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Use Case: UC-01 — Build Call Graph

**Actor:** System (triggered by project scan or file change) **Precondition:** AST and symbol data available from KSA-172 **Trigger:** Full project scan or incremental file update

#### Main Flow

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | Action | System Response |
| 1 | System | Request call graph build for project | Initialize empty directed graph |
| 2 | System | For each parsed file, extract call expressions from AST | Identify function/method calls |
| 3 | System | For each call expression, resolve target symbol | Match call to declaration using symbol table |
| 4 | System | Create edge from caller to callee | Add directed edge with metadata |
| 5 | System | Handle unresolved calls | Mark edge as “unresolved” with best-guess target |
| 6 | System | Index graph for fast lookup | Build node-to-edges index |

#### Alternative Flows

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Condition | Action |
| AF-01 | Call target is dynamic (reflection, eval) | Mark as unresolved, add to “dynamic\_calls” list |
| AF-02 | Call target is in external library (not in project) | Create external node, mark as “external” |
| AF-03 | Virtual method call (interface/abstract) | Create edges to ALL implementations (over-approximation) |
| AF-04 | Higher-order function (callback) | Create edge to parameter type if resolvable, else unresolved |

#### Exception Flows

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Condition | Action |
| EF-01 | AST parsing failed for file | Skip file, log warning, continue with other files |
| EF-02 | Symbol table incomplete | Build partial graph, mark affected nodes as “incomplete” |
| EF-03 | Memory limit exceeded | Stop graph construction, return partial graph with warning |

#### Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Rule | Description |
| BR-01 | Node ID format | {file\_path}::{symbol\_name} (e.g., src/main.kt::processData) |
| BR-02 | Edge deduplication | Only one edge per unique (caller, callee, call\_type) tuple |
| BR-03 | Self-calls | Self-recursive calls create self-loop edges |
| BR-04 | Constructor calls | new Foo() creates edge to Foo.constructor |
| BR-05 | Method chains | a.b().c() creates edges: caller→b, caller→c (not b→c) |

### 3.2 Use Case: UC-02 — Build Dependency Graph

**Actor:** System (triggered by project scan or file change) **Precondition:** Import statements extracted from AST **Trigger:** Full project scan or incremental file update

#### Main Flow

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | Action | System Response |
| 1 | System | Request dependency graph build | Initialize empty directed graph |
| 2 | System | For each file, extract import/require statements | Get import paths |
| 3 | System | Resolve each import path to actual file | Use import resolver from KSA-172 |
| 4 | System | Create edge from importing file to imported file | Add directed edge with import type |
| 5 | System | Handle re-exports | Track transitive dependencies |
| 6 | System | Index graph for fast lookup | Build file-to-dependencies index |

#### Alternative Flows

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Condition | Action |
| AF-01 | Import path unresolvable (external package) | Create external node, mark as “external” |
| AF-02 | Barrel file (index.ts re-exporting) | Create edges to both barrel and actual source |
| AF-03 | Dynamic import (import()) | Mark as “dynamic” edge |
| AF-04 | Conditional import (if/else) | Create edge regardless (static analysis) |

#### Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Rule | Description |
| BR-06 | Node ID format | File path relative to project root (e.g., src/utils/helper.kt) |
| BR-07 | Edge types | static\_import, dynamic\_import, re\_export, type\_only |
| BR-08 | Self-imports | Ignored (file importing itself) |
| BR-09 | Circular imports | Allowed in graph (detected separately by cycle detection) |

### 3.3 Use Case: UC-03 — Perform Impact Analysis

**Actor:** Developer or AI Agent (via MCP tool) **Precondition:** Call graph and/or dependency graph built **Trigger:** User queries impact of a change

#### Main Flow

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | Action | System Response |
| 1 | User | Request impact analysis for symbol/file | Validate input exists in graph |
| 2 | System | Determine analysis type (call-based or dependency-based) | Select appropriate graph |
| 3 | System | Find all direct dependents (in-edges) | Return immediate callers/importers |
| 4 | System | Traverse transitively up to depth limit | BFS from target, collecting all reachable |
| 5 | System | Calculate impact score for each affected node | Score = 1/distance + fan-out weight |
| 6 | System | Sort results by impact score (descending) | Return ranked list |

#### API Contract

**Request:**

{
 "tool": "graph\_impact\_analysis",
 "arguments": {
 "target": "src/services/UserService.kt::createUser",
 "type": "call\_graph",
 "depth": 3,
 "include\_external": false
 }
}

**Response:**

{
 "target": "src/services/UserService.kt::createUser",
 "total\_affected": 12,
 "direct\_dependents": 4,
 "transitive\_dependents": 8,
 "impact\_score": 0.85,
 "affected": [
 {
 "node": "src/controllers/UserController.kt::handleCreate",
 "distance": 1,
 "impact\_score": 1.0,
 "relationship": "direct\_caller"
 },
 {
 "node": "src/api/routes.kt::registerRoutes",
 "distance": 2,
 "impact\_score": 0.5,
 "relationship": "transitive\_caller"
 }
 ]
}

### 3.4 Use Case: UC-04 — Traverse Graph (BFS/DFS)

**Actor:** Developer or AI Agent (via MCP tool) **Precondition:** Graph built **Trigger:** User requests traversal

#### Main Flow

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | Action | System Response |
| 1 | User | Request traversal from start node | Validate start node exists |
| 2 | System | Initialize traversal with algorithm (BFS/DFS) | Create visited set, queue/stack |
| 3 | System | Execute traversal respecting depth limit | Visit nodes in order |
| 4 | System | Apply filter if specified | Skip nodes not matching filter |
| 5 | System | Collect traversal results | Return ordered list of visited nodes |

#### API Contract

**Request:**

{
 "tool": "graph\_traverse",
 "arguments": {
 "start": "src/main.kt::main",
 "algorithm": "bfs",
 "direction": "forward",
 "max\_depth": 5,
 "filter": { "package": "src/services" }
 }
}

**Response:**

{
 "start": "src/main.kt::main",
 "algorithm": "bfs",
 "direction": "forward",
 "nodes\_visited": 23,
 "max\_depth\_reached": 4,
 "results": [
 { "node": "src/services/UserService.kt::createUser", "depth": 1 },
 { "node": "src/services/AuthService.kt::authenticate", "depth": 1 },
 { "node": "src/services/UserService.kt::validateEmail", "depth": 2 }
 ]
}

### 3.5 Use Case: UC-05 — Detect Cycles

**Actor:** Developer or AI Agent (via MCP tool) **Precondition:** Graph built **Trigger:** User requests cycle detection or automated scan

#### Main Flow

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | Action | System Response |
| 1 | User | Request cycle detection | Select graph type (call/dependency) |
| 2 | System | Run Tarjan’s SCC algorithm | Find all strongly connected components |
| 3 | System | Filter SCCs with size > 1 | These are cycles |
| 4 | System | For each cycle, extract cycle path | Report A → B → C → A |
| 5 | System | Classify severity | Self-recursion=info, mutual=warning, circular deps=error |
| 6 | System | Return sorted by severity | Critical first |

#### API Contract

**Request:**

{
 "tool": "graph\_detect\_cycles",
 "arguments": {
 "graph\_type": "dependency",
 "scope": "src/",
 "min\_severity": "warning"
 }
}

**Response:**

{
 "total\_cycles": 3,
 "cycles": [
 {
 "id": "cycle-1",
 "severity": "error",
 "type": "circular\_dependency",
 "path": ["src/a.kt", "src/b.kt", "src/c.kt", "src/a.kt"],
 "length": 3
 },
 {
 "id": "cycle-2",
 "severity": "warning",
 "type": "mutual\_recursion",
 "path": ["src/parser.kt::parseExpr", "src/parser.kt::parseTerm", "src/parser.kt::parseExpr"],
 "length": 2
 }
 ]
}

