}

### 3.7 Use Case: UC-07 — Incremental Graph Update

**Actor:** System (triggered by file change event) **Precondition:** Graph already built, file re-parsed by KSA-172 **Trigger:** File save/edit detected

#### Main Flow

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | Action | System Response |
| 1 | System | Receive updated AST/symbols for changed file | Identify affected graph nodes |
| 2 | System | Remove all edges FROM changed file’s symbols | Clear outgoing call edges |
| 3 | System | Remove all edges TO deleted symbols | Clear incoming edges to removed functions |
| 4 | System | Re-extract calls from new AST | Build new edge set |
| 5 | System | Add new edges to graph | Merge with existing graph |
| 6 | System | Invalidate cached traversal results | Clear memoized paths |
| 7 | System | Update graph generation counter | Increment version |

#### Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Rule | Description |
| BR-10 | Incremental threshold | If > 30% of files changed, trigger full rebuild |
| BR-11 | Batch updates | Multiple file changes within 100ms are batched |
| BR-12 | Cache invalidation | Only invalidate paths that include changed nodes |

### 3.8 Use Case: UC-08 — Query Graph via MCP

**Actor:** AI Agent or IDE (via MCP protocol) **Precondition:** Graph built **Trigger:** MCP tool call received

#### MCP Tools Exposed

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Tool Name | Description | Input | Output |
| graph\_build | Build/rebuild graph for project | { path: string, type: "call"\|"dependency"\|"both" } | Build status |
| graph\_impact\_analysis | Analyze change impact | { target, type, depth } | Impact results |
| graph\_traverse | BFS/DFS traversal | { start, algorithm, direction, max\_depth, filter } | Traversal results |
| graph\_detect\_cycles | Find circular dependencies | { graph\_type, scope, min\_severity } | Cycle list |
| graph\_hot\_paths | Find most-called functions | { top\_n, scope, metric } | Ranked nodes |
| graph\_shortest\_path | Find shortest path between nodes | { from, to, graph\_type } | Path |
| graph\_stats | Get graph statistics | { graph\_type } | Node/edge counts |
| graph\_neighbors | Get immediate neighbors | { node, direction, graph\_type } | Neighbor list |

## 4. Data Specifications

### 4.1 Graph Node

data class GraphNode(
 val id: String, // Unique identifier (file::symbol or file path)
 val type: NodeType, // FUNCTION, CLASS, METHOD, FILE, MODULE, EXTERNAL
 val name: String, // Human-readable name
 val filePath: String, // Source file path
 val position: Position?, // Line/column in source (null for external)
 val language: String, // Programming language
 val visibility: Visibility?, // PUBLIC, PRIVATE, INTERNAL, PROTECTED
 val metadata: Map<String, Any> // Additional properties
)

enum class NodeType {
 FUNCTION, CLASS, METHOD, FILE, MODULE, EXTERNAL, CONSTRUCTOR, PROPERTY
}

### 4.2 Graph Edge

data class GraphEdge(
 val id: String, // Unique edge identifier
 val source: String, // Source node ID
 val target: String, // Target node ID
 val type: EdgeType, // CALL, IMPORT, EXTENDS, IMPLEMENTS
 val metadata: EdgeMetadata // Additional edge properties
)

enum class EdgeType {
 CALL, // Function/method call
 STATIC\_IMPORT, // Static import statement
 DYNAMIC\_IMPORT, // Dynamic import (import())
 RE\_EXPORT, // Re-export from barrel file
 TYPE\_ONLY, // Type-only import (no runtime)
 EXTENDS, // Class inheritance
 IMPLEMENTS, // Interface implementation
 UNRESOLVED // Could not resolve target
}

data class EdgeMetadata(
 val callType: CallType?, // DIRECT, VIRTUAL, CALLBACK, CONSTRUCTOR
 val confidence: Float, // 0.0-1.0 resolution confidence
 val sourcePosition: Position?, // Call site position
 val isConditional: Boolean // Inside if/switch branch
)

### 4.3 Graph Structure

data class CodeGraph(
 val type: GraphType, // CALL\_GRAPH, DEPENDENCY\_GRAPH
 val nodes: Map<String, GraphNode>,
 val edges: List<GraphEdge>,
 val adjacencyList: Map<String, List<String>>, // Forward edges
 val reverseAdjacencyList: Map<String, List<String>>, // Reverse edges
 val metadata: GraphMetadata
)

data class GraphMetadata(
 val projectPath: String,
 val totalFiles: Int,
 val totalNodes: Int,
 val totalEdges: Int,
 val buildTimeMs: Long,
 val generation: Int, // Incremented on each update
 val lastUpdated: Instant
)

## 5. Non-Functional Requirements

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Category | Requirement | Target | Measurement |
| Performance | Call graph build | < 10s for 1000 files | Benchmark suite |
| Performance | Dependency graph build | < 5s for 1000 files | Benchmark suite |
| Performance | Impact analysis query | < 500ms | Per-query timing |
| Performance | BFS/DFS traversal | < 100ms for 10K nodes | Per-query timing |
| Performance | Cycle detection | < 2s for 1000 files | Full scan timing |
| Performance | Incremental update | < 100ms per file | Single file change |
| Memory | Graph storage | < 500MB for 1000 files | Heap profiling |
| Accuracy | Static call resolution | > 85% for typed languages | Test fixture comparison |
| Accuracy | Import resolution | > 95% | Test fixture comparison |
| Parity | Output match with nodejs | > 99% | Automated comparison |
| Concurrency | Read queries | Thread-safe, lock-free reads | Concurrent test |
| Concurrency | Write updates | Serialized writes, no corruption | Stress test |

## 6. Error Handling

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Error Code | Condition | Response | Recovery |
| GRAPH\_001 | Graph not built yet | Return error with instruction to build | Auto-trigger build |
| GRAPH\_002 | Node not found in graph | Return empty result with warning | Suggest similar nodes |
| GRAPH\_003 | Traversal depth exceeded limit | Return partial results with truncation flag | Increase limit |
| GRAPH\_004 | Memory limit during build | Return partial graph | Suggest scope reduction |
| GRAPH\_005 | Circular reference in resolution | Break cycle, mark as unresolved | Log warning |
| GRAPH\_006 | Invalid graph type requested | Return validation error | List valid types |
| GRAPH\_007 | Concurrent modification | Retry with latest generation | Queue update |

